        </li>
        <li class="style2">
          <span class="icon fas fa-child"></span>
          <strong>1 in 13</strong> Children suffers
        </li>
        <li class="style3">
          <span class="icon fas fa-code-fork"></span>
          <strong>30 %</strong> Children allergic to more than one food
        </li>
        <li class="style4">
          <span class="icon fas fa-signal"></span>
          <strong>50 %</strong> Increased prevalance between 1997 and 2011.
        </li>
        <li class="style5">
          <span class="icon fas fa-stethoscope"></span>
          <strong>200,000</strong> people require emergency medical care for allergic reactions to food every year
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="content">A food allergy is a medical condition in which exposure to a food triggers a harmful immune response. The immune response, called an allergic reaction, occurs because the immune system attacks proteins in the food that are normally harmless. The proteins that trigger the reaction are called allergens.</p>
